{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a314bc97408580996","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Use WebSearch and WebFetch to research the LIMITATIONS / WHAT ALPHAEVOLVE CANNOT DO for Google DeepMind's AlphaEvolve (2025). I need specific, cited facts with exact source URLs and verbatim quotes.\n\nFocus on:\n- AlphaEvolve does NOT improve its own underlying LLMs / does not modify Gemini's weights (it is not recursive self-improvement of the model itself)\n- It REQUIRES an automated verifier/evaluator — it cannot be applied to problems lacking automated evaluation\n- The main limitation stated by DeepMind: it handles problems whose solutions can be \"described as algorithms\" and \"automatically evaluated\"; problems requiring manual experimentation are excluded\n- Any DeepMind caveats about scope, generality, future work\n- Any commentary on whether this is/isn't \"recursive self-improvement\" or AGI\n\nPrefer primary sources: deepmind.google blog post (\"AlphaEvolve a Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms\"), the arxiv/DeepMind white paper PDF (look at the Limitations and Conclusion sections). Also credible coverage (MIT Tech Review, Ars Technica, IEEE Spectrum) for how experts framed the limits.\n\nReturn a list of falsifiable, specific claims. Each claim MUST have its exact source URL. Quote DeepMind's own caveats VERBATIM where possible. Do not write files — return findings as your final text message."},"uuid":"8a83f959-fdd1-49ae-8bab-10bbf8667b7a","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:52.470Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
