{"parentUuid":"5106798e-d2ec-4890-a106-eb7dbeff0fa2","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a314bc97408580996","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_0113T8k7sHRujJDWdVtanFij","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NaYEPek1xHa1YAscanuH5H","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"AlphaEvolve does not improve own LLM not recursive self-improvement Gemini weights"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1003,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5903,"cache_read_input_tokens":6425,"output_tokens":154,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5903},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1003,"output_tokens":154,"cache_read_input_tokens":6425,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5903,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5903,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":8236}}},"requestId":"req_011CcG24qFrqwaVt35ZBeQ6R","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"7ae0f486-4129-4542-8084-db11ab8ab9b3","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:59.860Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"7ae0f486-4129-4542-8084-db11ab8ab9b3","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a314bc97408580996","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NaYEPek1xHa1YAscanuH5H","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AlphaEvolve does not improve own LLM not recursive self-improvement Gemini weights\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Recursive Self-Improvement. Future Dream or Current Reality? | by Ed Daniels | CodeX | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/codex/recursive-self-improvement-ae03d40e7cda\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: Gemini AI Powers Next-Gen Coding Agent | The Coders Blog | Home\",\"url\":\"https://thecodersblog.com/alphaevolve-gemini-powered-coding-agent-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery\",\"url\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/DeepMind.com/Blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/AlphaEvolve.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Overcoming LLM Performance Plateau: AlphaEvolve’s Evolutionary Approach to Continuous Gemini Enhancement | by Kishore Gopalan | Google Cloud - Community | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/google-cloud/overcoming-llm-performance-plateau-alphaevolves-evolutionary-approach-to-continuous-gemini-e5a22c64b540\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AlphaEvolve\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms — Google DeepMind\",\"url\":\"https://deepmind.google/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/\"},{\"title\":\"LLM-Guided Evolutionary Kernel Optimization: From Research to Production KernelsYep!\",\"url\":\"https://mlai.blog/2025-12-20-llm-kernel-optimization\"},{\"title\":\"Enhancing LLM Planning Capabilities through Intrinsic Self-Critique\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.24103\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found information about AlphaEvolve and its relationship with Gemini. Here are the key findings:\n\nAlphaEvolve is Google DeepMind's autonomous algorithm discovery system that uses Gemini models to generate, test, and iteratively refine algorithms. However, regarding the claim about self-improvement of the LLM weights:\n\nThe claim of full \"self-improvement\" often overlooks the critical human element in defining objective functions and providing the initial guidance that steers the LLM's evolutionary trajectory. This suggests that AlphaEvolve does not achieve true recursive self-improvement of the Gemini model weights themselves.\n\nWhile AlphaEvolve has improved the matrix multiplication kernel used to train the Gemini models that power AlphaEvolve, this is optimization of the training infrastructure and kernels, not direct improvement of the LLM's weights or core model parameters.\n\nAdditionally, the narrative of \"self-improvement\" needs careful dissection, indicating there is nuance and debate around whether AlphaEvolve truly achieves recursive self-improvement of the LLM itself. The system optimizes algorithms and infrastructure used in training, but this is distinct from the model directly improving its own weights in a recursive manner.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"3d0f11db-269e-4c7b-82d8-fcf8f30d5800","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:07.543Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"AlphaEvolve does not improve own LLM not recursive self-improvement Gemini weights","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01XiL1UpQkBiRVzBESiRntXJ","content":[{"title":"Recursive Self-Improvement. Future Dream or Current Reality? | by Ed Daniels | CodeX | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/codex/recursive-self-improvement-ae03d40e7cda"},{"title":"AlphaEvolve: Gemini AI Powers Next-Gen Coding Agent | The Coders Blog | Home","url":"https://thecodersblog.com/alphaevolve-gemini-powered-coding-agent-2026/"},{"title":"AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery","url":"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/DeepMind.com/Blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/AlphaEvolve.pdf"},{"title":"Overcoming LLM Performance Plateau: AlphaEvolve’s Evolutionary Approach to Continuous Gemini Enhancement | by Kishore Gopalan | Google Cloud - Community | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/google-cloud/overcoming-llm-performance-plateau-alphaevolves-evolutionary-approach-to-continuous-gemini-e5a22c64b540"},{"title":"AlphaEvolve - Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AlphaEvolve"},{"title":"AlphaEvolve: A Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms — Google DeepMind","url":"https://deepmind.google/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/"},{"title":"LLM-Guided Evolutionary Kernel Optimization: From Research to Production KernelsYep!","url":"https://mlai.blog/2025-12-20-llm-kernel-optimization"},{"title":"Enhancing LLM Planning Capabilities through Intrinsic Self-Critique","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.24103"}]},"Based on the search results, I found information about AlphaEvolve and its relationship with Gemini. Here are the key findings:\n\nAlphaEvolve is Google DeepMind's autonomous algorithm discovery system that uses Gemini models to generate, test, and iteratively refine algorithms. However, regarding the claim about self-improvement of the LLM weights:\n\nThe claim of full \"self-improvement\" often overlooks the critical human element in defining objective functions and providing the initial guidance that steers the LLM's evolutionary trajectory. This suggests that AlphaEvolve does not achieve true recursive self-improvement of the Gemini model weights themselves.\n\nWhile AlphaEvolve has improved the matrix multiplication kernel used to train the Gemini models that power AlphaEvolve, this is optimization of the training infrastructure and kernels, not direct improvement of the LLM's weights or core model parameters.\n\nAdditionally, the narrative of \"self-improvement\" needs careful dissection, indicating there is nuance and debate around whether AlphaEvolve truly achieves recursive self-improvement of the LLM itself. The system optimizes algorithms and infrastructure used in training, but this is distinct from the model directly improving its own weights in a recursive manner."],"durationSeconds":7.398574500000104,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"7ae0f486-4129-4542-8084-db11ab8ab9b3","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"5106798e-d2ec-4890-a106-eb7dbeff0fa2","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a314bc97408580996","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JiqsQ5nkmrue8k62uobrvj","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AlphaEvolve DeepMind limitations requires automated evaluator described as algorithms\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Can AlphaEvolve Change How We Solve Problems? A Look Inside DeepMind’s Latest Breakthrough - AIwire\",\"url\":\"https://www.hpcwire.com/aiwire/2025/05/27/can-alphaevolve-change-how-we-solve-problems-a-look-inside-deepminds-latest-breakthrough/\"},{\"title\":\"Can AlphaEvolve Change How We Solve Problems? A Look Inside DeepMind’s Latest Breakthrough\",\"url\":\"https://www.aiwire.net/2025/05/27/can-alphaevolve-change-how-we-solve-problems-a-look-inside-deepminds-latest-breakthrough/\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: Google DeepMind’s Groundbreaking Step Toward AGI\",\"url\":\"https://www.unite.ai/alphaevolve-google-deepminds-groundbreaking-step-toward-agi/\"},{\"title\":\"Can AlphaEvolve Change How We Solve Problems? A Look Inside DeepMind’s Latest Breakthrough - HPCwire\",\"url\":\"https://www.hpcwire.com/2025/06/02/can-alphaevolve-change-how-we-solve-problems-a-look-inside-deepminds-latest-breakthrough/\"},{\"title\":\"DeepMind’s AlphaEvolve Redefines Algorithm Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://www.turing.com/blog/exploring-alphaevolve\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery\",\"url\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/DeepMind.com/Blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/AlphaEvolve.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms — Google DeepMind\",\"url\":\"https://deepmind.google/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/\"},{\"title\":\"DeepMind Creates AlphaEvolve: An AI Agent That Invents - SmythOS\",\"url\":\"https://smythos.com/ai-trends/deepmind-creates-alphaevolve/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found regarding AlphaEvolve, DeepMind's limitations, and its requirement for automated evaluators:\n\n## Key Limitations\n\nAlphaEvolve has two key limitations. First, it can only tackle problems that come with a built-in way to evaluate success. This means that users must provide it with a formula or some method to automatically test its solutions.\n\nAlphaEvolve's current limitation is its dependence on automated evaluation functions. This confines its utility to problems that can be formalized mathematically or algorithmically.\n\n## Role of Automated Evaluators\n\nAlphaEvolve pairs the creative problem-solving capabilities of Gemini models with automated evaluators that verify answers, and uses an evolutionary framework to improve upon the most promising ideas. Each modified program is then tested using automated evaluators tailored to the task. The most effective candidates are stored, referenced, and recombined as inspiration for future iterations.\n\n## Practical Implications\n\nAlphaEvolve only works well in problems that can be clearly scored by code—limiting its use in fields like medicine or biology, where success often depends on human judgment or lab results. AlphaEvolve's success hinges on having reliable, automatable evaluation functions.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"cd8c2879-9883-4493-a317-548932eae416","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:08.138Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"AlphaEvolve DeepMind limitations requires automated evaluator described as algorithms","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01EPfByAvU7Aya3oqNf3Aoys","content":[{"title":"Can AlphaEvolve Change How We Solve Problems? A Look Inside DeepMind’s Latest Breakthrough - AIwire","url":"https://www.hpcwire.com/aiwire/2025/05/27/can-alphaevolve-change-how-we-