lly or algorithmically.\n\n## Role of Automated Evaluators\n\nAlphaEvolve pairs the creative problem-solving capabilities of Gemini models with automated evaluators that verify answers, and uses an evolutionary framework to improve upon the most promising ideas. Each modified program is then tested using automated evaluators tailored to the task. The most effective candidates are stored, referenced, and recombined as inspiration for future iterations.\n\n## Practical Implications\n\nAlphaEvolve only works well in problems that can be clearly scored by code—limiting its use in fields like medicine or biology, where success often depends on human judgment or lab results. AlphaEvolve's success hinges on having reliable, automatable evaluation functions."],"durationSeconds":8.575415082998573,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5106798e-d2ec-4890-a106-eb7dbeff0fa2","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
