{"parentUuid":"14d6e58a-7092-42b7-8e8f-8e1094a0f40f","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a314bc97408580996","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PSCJm7qMLgTJj72fqzXBPw","type":"tool_result","content":"# AlphaEvolve: Limitations and Scope\n\n## What AlphaEvolve Can Do\n\nAlphaEvolve is designed for \"any problem whose solution can be described as an algorithm, and automatically verified.\"\n\n## Key Requirements\n\nThe system requires **automated evaluation metrics** to work: \"These metrics provide an objective, quantifiable assessment of each solution's accuracy and quality.\"\n\n## Scope Limitations\n\nAlphaEvolve currently focuses on specific domains: \"While AlphaEvolve is currently being applied across math and computing, its general nature means it can be applied to any problem whose solution can be described as an algorithm, and automatically verified.\"\n\n## Future Potential\n\nThe developers note broader applications are possible: \"material science, drug discovery, sustainability and wider technological and business applications.\"\n\n## Dependency on LLM Improvement\n\nThe system's advancement is tied to underlying technology: \"we're expecting AlphaEvolve to continue improving alongside the capabilities of large language models.\"\n\n## Important Constraint\n\nThere is no mention of self-improvement capabilities, AGI potential, or autonomous recursive improvement. The system operates within a human-directed evolutionary framework where human developers set problems and evaluation criteria."}]},"uuid":"019669f1-0d84-4b89-857f-6c0dd588f657","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:17.706Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":151623,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# AlphaEvolve: Limitations and Scope\n\n## What AlphaEvolve Can Do\n\nAlphaEvolve is designed for \"any problem whose solution can be described as an algorithm, and automatically verified.\"\n\n## Key Requirements\n\nThe system requires **automated evaluation metrics** to work: \"These metrics provide an objective, quantifiable assessment of each solution's accuracy and quality.\"\n\n## Scope Limitations\n\nAlphaEvolve currently focuses on specific domains: \"While AlphaEvolve is currently being applied across math and computing, its general nature means it can be applied to any problem whose solution can be described as an algorithm, and automatically verified.\"\n\n## Future Potential\n\nThe developers note broader applications are possible: \"material science, drug discovery, sustainability and wider technological and business applications.\"\n\n## Dependency on LLM Improvement\n\nThe system's advancement is tied to underlying technology: \"we're expecting AlphaEvolve to continue improving alongside the capabilities of large language models.\"\n\n## Important Constraint\n\nThere is no mention of self-improvement capabilities, AGI potential, or autonomous recursive improvement. The system operates within a human-directed evolutionary framework where human developers set problems and evaluation criteria.","durationMs":4243,"url":"https://deepmind.google/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"14d6e58a-7092-42b7-8e8f-8e1094a0f40f","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
