{"parentUuid":"d0060c06-d37d-45cf-ab86-5574470f22e1","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a314bc97408580996","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017pBytJLACbpW2ehWDQ3yQx","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AlphaEvolve arxiv \"white paper\" limitations section conclusion automatic evaluator\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve | cbarkinozer | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://cbarkinozer.medium.com/alphaevolve-419242a0a4b4\"},{\"title\":\"[2506.13131] AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery\",\"url\":\"https://ar5iv.labs.arxiv.org/html/2506.13131\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/392736011_AlphaEvolve_A_coding_agent_for_scientific_and_algorithmic_discovery\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery\",\"url\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/DeepMind.com/Blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/AlphaEvolve.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"2025-5-16 AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery\",\"url\":\"https://msu.dvaoblaka.ru/media/2025/05/68271bf34ef55_AlphaEvolve.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Building Production-Ready Probes For Gemini\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.11516\"},{\"title\":\"Paper Review: AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery | by Andrew Lukyanenko | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://artgor.medium.com/paper-review-alphaevolve-a-coding-agent-for-scientific-and-algorithmic-discovery-5732a876c2e2\"},{\"title\":\"ImprovEvolve: Ask AlphaEvolve to Improve the Input Solution and Then Improvise\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.10233\"}]\n\nI found information about AlphaEvolve's limitations regarding the automatic evaluator. Here's what the white paper discusses:\n\n## Main Limitation\n\nThe main limitation of AlphaEvolve is that it handles problems for which it is possible to devise an automated evaluator, which is true of many problems in the mathematical and computational sciences, but there are domains such as the natural sciences where only some experiments can be simulated or automated.\n\nWhile the use of an automated evaluation metric offers AlphaEvolve a key advantage, it is also a limitation—in particular, it puts tasks that require manual experimentation out of scope.\n\n## Focus Areas\n\nBecause problems in mathematics, computer science, and system optimization typically permit automated evaluation metrics, efforts on AlphaEvolve focus on these domains.\n\n## Future Directions\n\nWhile AlphaEvolve does allow for LLM-provided evaluation of ideas, this is not a setting that has been optimized for, however, concurrent work shows this is possible, and a natural step would be to link the two settings, with LLMs providing feedback on high-level ideas before transitioning to an implementation stage.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"45936ef2-ef77-4345-bc10-8570710c0e92","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:34.248Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"AlphaEvolve arxiv \"white paper\" limitations section conclusion automatic evaluator","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01XYmyYNdwPyB827mpeC7MTQ","content":[{"title":"AlphaEvolve | cbarkinozer | Medium","url":"https://cbarkinozer.medium.com/alphaevolve-419242a0a4b4"},{"title":"[2506.13131] AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery","url":"https://ar5iv.labs.arxiv.org/html/2506.13131"},{"title":"(PDF) AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery","url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/392736011_AlphaEvolve_A_coding_agent_for_scientific_and_algorithmic_discovery"},{"title":"AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery","url":"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/DeepMind.com/Blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/AlphaEvolve.pdf"},{"title":"2025-5-16 AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery","url":"https://msu.dvaoblaka.ru/media/2025/05/68271bf34ef55_AlphaEvolve.pdf"},{"title":"Building Production-Ready Probes For Gemini","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.11516"},{"title":"Paper Review: AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery | by Andrew Lukyanenko | Medium","url":"https://artgor.medium.com/paper-review-alphaevolve-a-coding-agent-for-scientific-and-algorithmic-discovery-5732a876c2e2"},{"title":"ImprovEvolve: Ask AlphaEvolve to Improve the Input Solution and Then Improvise","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.10233"}]},"I found information about AlphaEvolve's limitations regarding the automatic evaluator. Here's what the white paper discusses:\n\n## Main Limitation\n\nThe main limitation of AlphaEvolve is that it handles problems for which it is possible to devise an automated evaluator, which is true of many problems in the mathematical and computational sciences, but there are domains such as the natural sciences where only some experiments can be simulated or automated.\n\nWhile the use of an automated evaluation metric offers AlphaEvolve a key advantage, it is also a limitation—in particular, it puts tasks that require manual experimentation out of scope.\n\n## Focus Areas\n\nBecause problems in mathematics, computer science, and system optimization typically permit automated evaluation metrics, efforts on AlphaEvolve focus on these domains.\n\n## Future Directions\n\nWhile AlphaEvolve does allow for LLM-provided evaluation of ideas, this is not a setting that has been optimized for, however, concurrent work shows this is possible, and a natural step would be to link the two settings, with LLMs providing feedback on high-level ideas before transitioning to an implementation stage."],"durationSeconds":8.2