{"parentUuid":"9c36e4b3-a741-4ba4-a5aa-29956d092859","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a314bc97408580996","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01GAuUeVM5NGNYXC2d3Kkud3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UKvoPUwNNspGMqmWt6cmgD","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"AlphaEvolve MIT Technology Review Ars Technica IEEE Spectrum limitations not AGI self-improvement"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1657,"cache_read_input_tokens":20213,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1657,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcG28crLwzdUwCWu9q74z","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"f72bb1a3-d912-478c-bbc3-78755348d8c7","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:50.423Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"f72bb1a3-d912-478c-bbc3-78755348d8c7","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b83cd85c-215e-4dfb-b12b-82fa27341e0f","agentId":"a314bc97408580996","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UKvoPUwNNspGMqmWt6cmgD","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AlphaEvolve MIT Technology Review Ars Technica IEEE Spectrum limitations not AGI self-improvement\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"What is Recursive Self-Improvement in AI? Alpha Evolve Explained - Geeky Gadgets\",\"url\":\"https://www.geeky-gadgets.com/alpha-evolve-ai-recursive-learning/\"},{\"title\":\"What Is Alpha Evolve? Google’s Self-Improving AI Explained - Geeky Gadgets\",\"url\":\"https://www.geeky-gadgets.com/alpha-evolve-googles-new-self-improving-ai-model-that-teaches-itself/\"},{\"title\":\"Recursive self-improvement - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recursive_self-improvement\"},{\"title\":\"What Is AlphaEvolve? How Google's AI Is Already Improving Its Own Training | MindStudio\",\"url\":\"https://www.mindstudio.ai/blog/what-is-alphaevolve-google-ai-self-improvement-2\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Improving AI Models: How AI Upgrades Itself? - هوش مصنوعی\",\"url\":\"https://deepfa.ir/en/blog/self-improving-ai-models\"},{\"title\":\"A Self-Improving Coding Agent\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2504.15228v2\"},{\"title\":\"How Google Created an AI That Improves Itself\",\"url\":\"https://www.thealgorithmicbridge.com/p/how-google-created-an-ai-that-improves\"},{\"title\":\"The AI Risk Spectrum: From Dangerous Capabilities to Existential Threats\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2508.13700\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about AlphaEvolve's limitations and its relationship to self-improvement versus AGI:\n\n## Key Limitations of AlphaEvolve\n\nDespite its impressive accomplishments, AlphaEvolve's reliance on human-defined problems and evaluation metrics restricts its autonomy, as it cannot independently identify or define new challenges.\n\nThe system relies on programmatically verifiable evaluation metrics, which restricts its ability to handle tasks requiring subjective judgment or manual experimentation. A key limitation is the need for automated evaluation functions.\n\n## Self-Improvement vs. AGI Status\n\nWhile AlphaEvolve demonstrates recursive self-improvement capabilities, it fits a careful version of recursive self-improvement definition, and is a sign that it's already happening, in a measured and controlled way, right now. However, while challenges remain, its development represents a significant step toward the realization of artificial general intelligence (AGI). This indicates AlphaEvolve is not itself AGI, but rather a step in that direction.\n\nThe search results didn't contain coverage from the specific sources you mentioned (MIT Technology Review, Ars Technica, or IEEE Spectrum) regarding AlphaEvolve's limitations.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"172ac3db-51a7-4811-8abb-e47f8848b8b4","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:57.425Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"AlphaEvolve MIT Technology Review Ars Technica IEEE Spectrum limitations not AGI self-improvement","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01KFfxsC2p3pHRuKb9693DtT","content":[{"title":"What is Recursive Self-Improvement in AI? Alpha Evolve Explained - Geeky Gadgets","url":"https://www.geeky-gadgets.com/alpha-evolve-ai-recursive-learning/"},{"title":"What Is Alpha Evolve? Google’s Self-Improving AI Explained - Geeky Gadgets","url":"https://www.geeky-gadgets.com/alpha-evolve-googles-new-self-improving-ai-model-that-teaches-itself/"},{"title":"Recursive self-improvement - Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recursive_self-improvement"},{"title":"What Is AlphaEvolve? How Google's AI Is Already Improving Its Own Training | MindStudio","url":"https://www.mindstudio.ai/blog/what-is-alphaevolve-google-ai-self-improvement-2"},{"title":"Self-Improving AI Models: How AI Upgrades Itself? - هوش مصنوعی","url":"https://deepfa.ir/en/blog/self-improving-ai-models"},{"title":"A Self-Improving Coding Agent","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2504.15228v2"},{"title":"How Google Created an AI That Improves Itself","url":"https://www.thealgorithmicbridge.com/p/how-google-created-an-ai-that-improves"},{"title":"The AI Risk Spectrum: From Dangerous Capabilities to Existential Threats","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2508.13700"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about AlphaEvolve's limitations and its relationship to self-improvement versus AGI:\n\n## Key Limitations of AlphaEvolve\n\nDespite its impressive accomplishments, AlphaEvolve's reliance on human-defined problems and evaluation metrics restricts its autonomy, as it cannot independently identify or define new challenges.\n\nThe system relies on programmatically verifiable evaluation metrics, which restricts its ability to handle tasks requiring subjective judgment or manual experimentation. A key limitation is the need for automated evaluation functions.\n\n## Self-Improvement vs. AGI Status\n\nWhile AlphaEvolve demonstrates recursive self-improvement capabilities, it fits a careful version of recursive self-improvement definition, and is a sign that it's already happening, in a measured and controlled way, right now. However, while challenges remain, its development represents a significant step toward the realization of artificial general intelligence (AGI). This indicates AlphaEvolve is not itself AGI, but rather a step in that direction.\n\nThe search results didn't contain coverage from the specific sources you mentioned (MIT Technology Review, Ars Technica, or IEEE Spectrum) regarding AlphaEvolve's limitations."],"durationSeconds":6.7091862499993296,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f72bb1a3-d912-478c-bbc3-78755348d8c7","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-